    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-08T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-08T05:00:00-05:00" n="641"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5206</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-08T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 8, 1.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram March 26, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d641fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_422">p. 422</ref>.</note>
                    Though United States is not formally party to the agreement excluding Chinese
                    troops from Tientsin because not at the time represented by military commander
                    there, yet we are now cooperating in the protection of Mukden Railway and,
                    therefore, I beg to request your instructions whether, in order not [?] to avoid
                    danger of conflicts, the exclusion of Chinese troops from the two unlikely [<hi
                        rend="italic">protective?</hi>] zones along railway, guarded by foreign
                    troops, may be enforced by us jointly with other powers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
